group-chatmod:
A user right group named '''Chat Moderators'''; this group moderates any chat that occurs in ''Special:Chat'' (a special page implemented by the [[mw:Extension:MediaWikiChat|MediaWikiChat extension]]). 
See also:
*{{msg-mw|group-chatmod-member}}

group-chatmod-member:
This describes what a member is called if they're in the Chat Moderators user group.
See also:
* {{msg-mw|group-chatmod}}

group-functionary:
A user right group named '''Functionary''', which contains multiple rights related to handling private data.
See also:
* {{msg-mw|group-functionary-member}}

group-functionary-member:
This describes what a member is called if they're in the Functionary user group.
See also:
* {{msg-mw|group-functionary}}

grouppage-functionary:
This describes how the project title about the '''Functionary''' user group is called.
See also
* {{msg-mw|group-functionary-member}}

parents:
This describes how the link label to Project:Parents on Brickipedia is called.
See also
*{{msg-mw|parentspage}}

termsofuse:
This describes how the link label for the 'Terms of Use' page, a policy that someone needs to abide to in order to use a service, is called.
See also
*{{msg-mw|termsofusepage}}

termsofusepage:
This describes how the project title for the '''Terms of Use''' policy is called.
See also
*{{msg-mw|termsofuse}}
